[LC] Create Learning Card — 6 steps to capture what was tested, what was learned, and what it implies. Takes ~20 minutes. The cohort, the metric drop, the hypothesis it disconfirms, and the open questions all get recorded.
[PP] Pivot, Patch, or Persevere — if the question is really "what do we do next," this is the structured frame. A 3% adverse effect usually points to patch (refine the variable) or pivot (rethink the assumption), rarely shelve.
